overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application,
  providing a detailed specification for its interactive features, report
  generation, data capture, and sleep disorder detection. The assistant
  conducted a thorough review, identifying several critical gaps in the existing
  implementation. Following this, the assistant proceeded to implement key
  high-priority features. This included integrating a 1-10 severity scale for
  tiredness interference, complete with safety warnings for high scores. Logic
  for detecting and reporting Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome was added, along with tailored recommendations.
  Finally, a "Resources & Next Steps" section was incorporated into the reports,
  providing placeholder outbound links to relevant external resources. These
  changes involved updates to data types, validation schemas, UI components, and
  both web and PDF report generation logic.
